							| .
						p
							| While discovering this beautiful intersection between aesthetics and logic, I got hooked and skipped my usual metro stop. I decided to take on a different path and follow a new born passion, so I left adidas and signed up for a full-time Web Development Course at 
							span.underlined
								a(href='https://nycda.com/amsterdam', target='_blank') New York Code and Design Academy in Amsterdam
							| . In Autumn 2017 I took on my first role as Web Developer Intern at Design & Technology agency 'Your Majesty', where I now work as Junior Web Developer.
						p
							| I have been working on both front- and back-end development, while generally trying to move into a more object oriented, modular programming style. I'm also learning more about software architectural patterns like the Model-view-controller, and how to best set up your data-flow. The focus of my interest sits around data and data visualisation, where I enjoy most to provide all necessary data-endpoints.
